Wisconsin Voter Alliance Update

The Beat Goes on in Green Bay ‚Äì Corrupt Mayor and his staff
The City of Green Bay continues to be a problem because Mayor Genrich and his left leaning staff seem to think they are above the law.  First it was the Zuckerbucks, illegal drop boxes and illegal GOTV activities in the 2020 election.  Then in 2022, the City Clerk Celestine Jeffreys introduced her own idea as to what was required for election observers setting her rules for observation.  She got her hands slapped on that, but she and Genrich just won‚Äôt abide by the laws that most other officials are compelled to do. Now they have installed illegal recording devices in City Hall, you can read the entire sordid details here City of Green Bay‚Äôs Illegal Recording Devices .  

Another issue on Green Bay.  Last week on the city council agenda was the issue of flying other flags alongside the U.S. Flag. Well, it came down to a 3 to 3 tie, so Mayor Genrich broke the tie and voted in favor of flying the LGBTQUIA+ flag at the City Hall.  This opens up a plethora of questions in my mind.  What about the Irish American flag, the Italian American Flag, etc., etc.  This is yet another nonsensical decision by the City of Green Bay.


Kenosha Unified School District (KUSD) conduct purge and cancels a Conservative Board Member
This is quite the story of KUSD arbitrarily purging an elected conservative from their school board.  Eric Meadows ran for a three-year term on the KUSD in April of 2022.  He was elected, and began his term on the board.  However, the leadership of KUSD had made a mistake when they ran the election. 

Basically the mistake they made resulted from an existing school board member resigning in midterm.  So the School District (not the board), decided to run the election for three new members, Eric‚Äôs term was allegedly for a 3 year term.  After the fact, they recognized their mistake and then without discussion determined that Eric would have to be the one removed from the board.

The decision to purge Eric was not an arbitrary decision as Eric had been involved in pursuing some changes to board member salaries and was, in general, the conservative voice on the board. So, Thomas More Society has taken on this election integrity case to protect Eric Meadows position on the board. At a minimum, there should be or have been some discussion or process followed to determine who is removed.  Remember this mistake was made by the KUSD, and it is not fair or correct legally to purge the school board of the one dissenting voice on the board.  
A cease and desist letter has been sent to KUSD as well as the Board Members.  A rally is planned at the KUSD on Tuesday, Feb 14th at KUSD.  We‚Äôll keep you posted on these developments.


City of Madison Landlord needed as Plaintiff
In my last update I mentioned the Madison city Ordinance 32.06 (5) which deals with landlords in the city being required to assist in expanding voter participation. Once again, here is the copied requirement of that ordinance; Voter Registration Forms . In order to increase citizen participation in elections, and in light of the many tenants residing in the City of Madison, every landlord shall provide a tenant with a voter registration form at the time the tenant takes possession of the residence. The voter registration form shall be the form made available by the City Clerk or as downloaded from the City Clerk's website. The landlord shall also provide each residential unit with the "How to Register" information available from the City Clerk. (Cr by ORD-12-00096, 7-27-12)
 
This is not legal for the city to compel landlords to execute this responsibility.  It has been defeated in other states and we will work to get this ordinance stricken from the books in Madison.
